# Game Testing Patterns

Skill for testing SCPB game functionality including SCP behaviors, inventory, and save/load systems.

## When to Use

Use this skill when:
- Writing tests for game mechanics
- Verifying SCP entity behaviors
- Testing inventory interactions
- Testing save/load functionality
- Regression testing after changes

## SCP Behavior Testing

### SCP-173 (Observation Test)

```blitzbasic
Function Test_SCP173_Observation()
    ; Setup
    npc = CreateNPC(NPC_SCP_173)
    PositionEntity npc\obj, 0, 0, -10

    ; Test: NPC frozen when observed
    Position Camera, 0, 5, 5
    PointEntity Camera, npc\obj
    UpdateNPCs()
    AssertEqual(npc\State, STATE_IDLE, "SCP-173 should freeze when observed")

    ; Test: NPC moves when not observed
    RotateEntity Camera, 0, 180, 0  ; Look away
    UpdateNPCs()  ; Multiple frames
    AssertNotEqual(npc\obj, startPos, "SCP-173 should move when not observed")

    ; Test: Snap on proximity
    PositionEntity Player, 0, 0, 2
    LookAwayFrom(npc)
    UpdateNPCs()
    Assert(PlayerDead(), "Player should die when SCP-173 gets close")
End Function
```

### SCP-096 (Viewed Test)

```blitzbasic
Function Test_SCP096_Trigger()
    ; Setup
    npc = CreateNPC(NPC_SCP_096)
    npc\State = STATE_DOCILE

    ; Test: Triggered by screenshot
    TakeScreenshot()
    WaitFrame(10)
    AssertEqual(npc\State, STATE_AGITATED, "SCP-096 should react to screenshot")

    ; Test: Instant kill in view
    PositionEntity Player, 0, 0, -5
    LookAt(npc)
    UpdateNPCs()
    Assert(PlayerDead(), "Player should die instantly when viewing SCP-096")

    ; Test: Cannot stop pursuit
    Distance(npc, Player) > 50
    AssertEqual(npc\State, STATE_PURSUIT, "SCP-096 cannot stop pursuit")
End Function
```

### SCP-106 (Corrosion Test)

```blitzbasic
Function Test_SCP106_Corrosion()
    ; Setup
    npc = CreateNPC(NPC_SCP_106)
    npc\State = STATE_HUNTING

    ; Test: Corrosion damage over time
    PositionEntity Player, 5, 0, 5
    UpdateNPCs()  ; Multiple frames while in range
    Assert(PlayerHealth() < 100, "Player should take corrosion damage")

    ; Test: Pocket dimension pull
    PositionEntity Player, 1, 0, 1  ; Very close
    UpdateNPCs()
    Assert(PlayerInPocketDimension(), "Player should be pulled into dimension")
End Function
```

### SCP-049 (Cure/Test Test)

```blitzbasic
Function Test_SCP049_Behavior()
    ; Setup
    npc = CreateNPC(NPC_SCP_049)
    npc\State = STATE_IDLE

    ; Test: Approaches player
    PositionEntity Player, 10, 0, 10
    UpdateNPCs()  ; Multiple frames
    Assert(Distance(npc, Player) < 8, "SCP-049 should approach player")

    ; Test: Demands cure
    AssertSaid("I must cure you of your pestilence", "SCP-049 should speak")

    ; Test: Touch kills
    PositionEntity Player, 1, 0, 1
    UpdateNPCs()
    Assert(PlayerDead(), "Touch should kill player")

    ; Test: Revival as SCP-049-2
    Assert(SpawnedSCP0492(), "SCP-049-2 should spawn after death")
End Function
```

### SCP-939 (Voice Mimicry Test)

```blitzbasic
Function Test_SCP939_VoiceMimic()
    ; Setup
    npc = CreateNPC(NPC_SCP_939)

    ; Test: Mimics other SCP voices
    npc\MimicTarget = NPC_SCP_173
    UpdateNPCs()
    Assert(PlayedSound("scp173_breath"), "Should mimic SCP-173 sound")

    ; Test: Mimics dead SCP-049-2
    npc\MimicTarget = NPC_SCP_049_2
    UpdateNPCs()
    Assert(PlayedSound("scp0492_screech"), "Should mimic SCP-049-2 sound")
End Function
```

## Inventory Testing

### Item Pickup Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_ItemPickup()
    ; Setup
    item = CreateItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED, 0, 0, -5)
    PositionEntity Player, 0, 0, 0

    ; Test: Auto-pickup on collision
    MoveEntity Player, 0, 0, -5
    UpdateItems()
    Assert(PlayerHasItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED), "Item should be picked up")

    ; Test: Item removed from world
    Assert(EntityDeleted(item\obj), "Item entity should be deleted")
End Function
```

### Item Combination Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_ItemCombination()
    ; Setup
    item1 = CreateItem(ITEM_BATTERY, 0, 0, 0)
    item2 = CreateItem(ITEM_FLASHLIGHT, 0, 0, 0)
    SelectItem(item1)

    ; Test: Valid combination
    CombineWith(item2)
    Assert(PlayerHasItem(ITEM_WORKING_FLASHLIGHT), "Should create working flashlight")

    ; Test: Invalid combination
    ClearSelection()
    SelectItem(item1)
    CombineWith(CreateItem(ITEM_2999_BEVERAGE))
    Assert(PlayerInventoryUnchanged(), "Invalid combo should not work")
End Function
```

### Drag and Drop Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_InventoryDragDrop()
    ; Setup
    AddItemToInventory(ITEM_MEDKIT, 0)
    AddItemToInventory(ITEM_BANDAGE, 1)

    ; Test: Drag changes position
    DragItem(0, 2)
    Assert(ItemAtSlot(2) == ITEM_MEDKIT, "Item should move to slot 2")

    ; Test: Swap items
    DragItem(2, 1)
    Assert(ItemAtSlot(1) == ITEM_MEDKIT And ItemAtSlot(2) == ITEM_BANDAGE, "Items should swap")
End Function
```

## Save/Load Testing

### Save Integrity Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_SaveIntegrity()
    ; Setup game state
    SetPlayerHealth(75)
    SetPlayerStamina(50)
    SetSanity(80)
    AddItemToInventory(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED)
    KillNPC(NPC_SCP_173)
    SetPlayerRoom(ROOM_LCZ_914)

    ; Test: Save preserves state
    SaveGame(0)
    Assert(SaveFileValid(0), "Save file should be created")

    ; Test: Load restores state
    LoadGame(0)
    AssertEqual(PlayerHealth(), 75, "Health should restore")
    AssertEqual(PlayerStamina(), 50, "Stamina should restore")
    AssertEqual(Sanity(), 80, "Sanity should restore")
    Assert(PlayerHasItem(ITEM_KEYCARD_RED), "Inventory should restore")
    Assert(NPCDead(NPC_SCP_173), "NPC state should restore")
    AssertEqual(PlayerRoom(), ROOM_LCZ_914, "Room should restore")
End Function
```

### Multi-Slot Save Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_MultipleSaveSlots()
    ; Create different game states
    SetPlayerHealth(100)
    SaveGame(0)

    SetPlayerHealth(50)
    SaveGame(1)

    ; Test: Slots are independent
    LoadGame(0)
    AssertEqual(PlayerHealth(), 100, "Slot 0 should have full health")

    LoadGame(1)
    AssertEqual(PlayerHealth(), 50, "Slot 1 should have damaged state")
End Function
```

### Corrupted Save Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_CorruptedSave()
    ; Setup corrupted file
    WriteString("save0.sav", "CORRUPTED DATA")

    ; Test: Graceful failure
    LoadGame(0)
    Assert(ShowedError("Corrupted save file"), "Should show error")
    Assert(GameStateUnchanged(), "Current game should not change")
End Function
```

## Game State Testing

### Room Transition Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_RoomTransition()
    ; Setup
    SetPlayerRoom(ROOM_LCZ_012)
    SetPlayerPosition(5, 0, 10)  ; Near door

    ; Test: Transition via door
    MoveThroughDoor(0)
    AssertEqual(PlayerRoom(), ROOM_LCZ_013, "Should transition to adjacent room")
    Assert(PlayerPositionNearDoor(0), "Player should be at door in new room")

    ; Test: NPCs don't follow (unless they should)
    npc = CreateNPC(NPC_SCP_173)
    PositionEntity npc\obj, 10, 0, 10
    MoveThroughDoor(0)
    Assert(NPCInOriginalRoom(npc), "NPCs should not follow through doors")
End Function
```

### Time-Based Events Test

```blitzbasic
Function Test_TimeBasedEvents()
    ; Setup
    SetTime(0)

    ; Test: MTF ambush at 6 minutes
    AdvanceTime(360)  ; 6 minutes
    Assert(EventTriggered("MTF_Ambush"), "MTF should ambush at 6 minutes")

    ; Test: SCP-173 gets faster over time
    ResetGame()
    StartTime()
    AdvanceTime(300)  ; 5 minutes
    initialSpeed = GetSCP173Speed()
    AdvanceTime(300)  ; 10 minutes
    Assert(GetSCP173Speed() > initialSpeed, "SCP-173 should speed up")
End Function
```

## Testing Utilities

```blitzbasic
Global TestAsserts%[1000]
Global TestAssertCount%
Global TestPassed%
Global TestFailed%

Function AssertEqual(actual#, expected#, message$)
    TestAssertCount = TestAssertCount + 1
    If Abs(actual - expected) < 0.01
        TestPassed = TestPassed + 1
    Else
        TestFailed = TestFailed + 1
        Print "FAIL: " + message + " (expected " + expected + ", got " + actual + ")"
    End If
End Function

Function AssertTrue(condition%, message$)
    TestAssertCount = TestAssertCount + 1
    If condition
        TestPassed = TestPassed + 1
    Else
        TestFailed = TestFailed + 1
        Print "FAIL: " + message
    End If
End Function

Function AssertFalse(condition%, message$)
    AssertTrue(Not condition, message)
End Function

Function Test_Suite_Run(suite$)
    Select suite$
        Case "SCP_Behaviors": RunSCPBehaviorTests()
        Case "Inventory": RunInventoryTests()
        Case "SaveLoad": RunSaveLoadTests()
        Case "All": RunAllTests()
    End Select

    Print "Tests: " + TestPassed + "/" + TestAssertCount + " passed"
    If TestFailed > 0
        Print TestFailed + " tests failed!"
    End If
End Function
```

## Test Execution

```blitzbasic
; Run individual test
Test_SCP173_Observation()

; Run test suite
Test_Suite_Run("SCP_Behaviors")
Test_Suite_Run("Inventory")
Test_Suite_Run("SaveLoad")

; Run all tests
Test_Suite_Run("All")
```

## Common Test Patterns

| Scenario | Pattern |
|----------|---------|
| NPC state changes | Check state before and after update |
| Player death | Verify health, death animation, game over |
| Item pickup | Check inventory, world entity deleted |
| Room transition | Verify room ID, player position, NPC locations |
| Save/load | Compare all relevant globals before and after |
| Time events | Advance time and check trigger conditions |
| Collision | Check collision callbacks and damage |
| Animation | Check animation frame, speed, looping |
